# No Em Dashes in Website Copy

Never use em dashes (—, `\u2014`, `&mdash;`) in any user-facing copy: bios, headlines, descriptions, button labels, taglines, toasts, etc.

Rewrite with a period, comma, colon, or restructure the sentence instead.

```text
❌ He began at 20—flipping properties while in school.
✅ He began at 20, flipping properties while in school.

❌ Great agents are made, not found—that idea built ASG.
✅ Great agents are made, not found. That idea built ASG.
```

This applies to copy in HTML, strings in inline JavaScript, and any text rendered to visitors. Code comments are exempt.
